## 7. Scoring Guide

For each question, score 1-4:

| Score | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 1 | Cannot answer or fundamentally wrong |
| 2 | Partial answer, knows basics but gaps in depth |
| 3 | Solid answer, demonstrates hands-on experience |
| 4 | Exceptional — goes beyond the question, shows deep understanding and judgment |

### Minimum Bar for Staff Level:
- Average score of 3.0 or higher across all questions
- No score of 1 on any question
- At least two scores of 4
- Must score 3+ on Q4 (NFS/network debugging), Q5 (SCC/security), and Q7 (secrets management) — these are core to the role

### Strong Hire Indicators:
- Tells stories from real production experience, not textbook answers
- Mentions monitoring/observability without being asked
- Thinks about cost and efficiency unprompted
- Asks clarifying questions before answering (shows engineering judgment)
- Can explain trade-offs, not just solutions

### No-Hire Indicators:
- Repeatedly suggests "just give it admin/privileged access"
- Cannot troubleshoot systematically (guesses randomly)
- No awareness of security context or multi-tenancy
- Cannot explain why, only what
- Claims expertise but answers are surface-level
